As the number of victims of the gas explosion that rocked Ajegunle, Ajeromi Ifelodun Local Council of Lagos State, lawmaker representing the area in the House of Representatives, Mr. Kolawole Taiwo, has harped on the need for government to enforce strict regulatory measures, and monitor the setting up of gas plants in the country. At least two persons were reported dead, with over 20 others seriously injured in the explosion, which occurred last Wednesday.
 
Taiwo, a former deputy speaker of Lagos State House of Assembly said it has become imperative for government at all levels to discourage the establishment of gas plants in residential areas following nasty experiences of gas explosions that have occurred in various parts of the country in recent times.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .